-- Chile’s Supreme Court Grants Injunction Against Endesa Plant
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-06-16T17:58:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-16/chile-s-supreme-court-grants-injunction-against-endesa-plant.html
Chile’s  Supreme Court  granted an
injunction filed by fishermen against Empresa Nacional de
Electricidad SA’s Bocamina II thermal plant project, the court
said, according to the judiciary’s  website .  Endesa, as Chile’s largest power generator is known, should
carry out an environmental impact study on the possible effects
of the project, the court said.  The plant is scheduled to begin operations in the second
half of this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
